  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Response to affected population through cash transfert in Chetimari and Gagamari</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The present project is intended to provide emergency support to 5,600 conflict affected people in Chetimari and Gagamari, Diffa region Niger affected by the attack of Bokoharam in Damasak (Nigeria). WHH and CWW are actively present in the crisis area and willing to provide their expertise in terms of Food Security and Livelihoods through multi-purpose cash distibutions as well as WASH community awareness activities. Affected population present high vulnerabilities and as markets are still funtionning, the response proposed aims at bringing rapid and efficient solutions to displaced populaitons that lost their livelihoods and sources of food due to the crisis. The imminent action to undertake is the distribution of unconditional CASH and carry out community awareness on hygiene and sanitation to help communities recover quickly their dignity: have safe access to food items that respond to their preferences and access clean water and sanitary conditions. Several households are sleeping under trees and do not have access to food and this situation can rapidly lead them in malnutrition. In terms of Sanitation and Hygiene, displaced populations are living presently in a very poor sanitation and hygiene conditions risky for their health, WHH and CWW will provide sensitization on hygiene and sanitation for affected population, sensitization on good practices for chlidren care (breasfeeding, good nutrition practices and prevention of malnutrition).</narrative>
  </description>
